Description: The first integer or pointer return value is placed in RAX.
The second integer return value is placed in RDX.
The first floating-point return value is placed in XMM0.
The second floating-point return value is placed in XMM1.
Additional integer return values (if any) are returned in memory
column4: with the caller allocating space for them.

Description: Additional floating-point return values (if any) are returned in memory
column4: with the caller allocating space for them.
